1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new pattern matching algorithm on a compact text index based on sparse suffix trees. This falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms.
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The proposed algorithm can be used for efficient text search and retrieval, which is a key area of information retrieval.
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the partitioning of text into blocks of equal size, which is a concept from discrete mathematics.
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the packing of several letters into one computer word, which can have implications on the computational complexity of the algorithm.
5. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) - The proposed algorithm can be used for efficient indexing and retrieval of text in digital libraries.
